<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-549-383  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 549 383.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Sept 24 1990 v7 n39 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC adopts revised LEC price caps. (Federal CommunicationsCommission, local exchange carriers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taff, Anita.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) will implement pricecaps for local exchange carriers on Jan 1, 1991.andP;  The plan couldsave consumers up to $2.5 billion on local carrier interstateaccess and operator services during the next four years.andP;  Such acost reduction could triple the predictions made by the FCC in1987 when the plan was introduced.andP;  The increased savings, due tomodifications in the plan, ensure that users will benefit from thenew regulations.andP;  The FCC also lowered the rate of return for alllocal carriers by almost one percent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Profit MarginPriceCost ReductionUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionTelecommunications ServicesCommunications Service SuppliersGovernment RegulationBell Regional Holding Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>